===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|conneccioun}}, {{m|enm|connexioun}}, {{m|enm|conneccyon}}, {{m|enm|conneccion}}, from {{der|en|la|connexionem}} (nominative {{m|la|connexio||a [[conclusion]], [[binding]] [[together]]}}), from {{m|la|connectō}}, an alternative spelling of {{m|la|cōnectō||I [[bind]] [[together]]}}, from compound of {{m|la|co-||[[together]]}} and {{m|la|nectō||I [[bind]]}}

In [[American English]] mid-18c., spelling shifted from {{m|en|connexion}} to ''connection'' (equivalent to {{suffix|en|connect|ion}}), thus making {{m|en|connexion}} British dated and ''connection'' in international use.

